      "writtenOn": "2021-06-22T14:00:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I wonder if we would be better off having some sort of inert error expression that we can pass around, instead of adding null checks everywhere. e.g. we have Nop to return from the Switch convert if we went off the rails, rather than returning null. Do we need a Nop expression? (would it be sufficient to use `ExpressionType(0)`?)",
      "revId": "a62ab40f2e7ae14017fa97ea1cdad633c6975074",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
