        "id": 5640
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-22T17:34:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I considered that, but the issue is that we\u0027ll still have to pass type checks everywhere if I do that - that dummy expression will have to have the right type to be accepted wherever it\u0027s being used, at least if we want to avoid adding a ton of extra checks on the SkSL side of things.\n\nIt seemed like just tossing in a few null checks and keeping all of the changes confined to DSL was probably safer and easier.",
      "parentUuid": "1f2b8062_fe177a79",
      "revId": "a62ab40f2e7ae14017fa97ea1cdad633c6975074",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
